article.description: — Divante Moffitt scored 22 points shooting 9 for 13 and Isaac Jones scored 17 points and Idaho pulled away in the back end of the first half and Idaho beat Northern Illinois 84-47 on Friday night.
article.headline: Idaho's 2nd-half blitz leads to 84-47 ripping of N. Illinois
article.linkText: Idaho's 2nd-half blitz leads to 84-47 ripping of N. Illinois
article.story: MOSCOW, Idaho -- — Divante Moffitt scored 22 points shooting 9 for 13 and Isaac Jones scored 17 points and Idaho pulled away in the back end of the first half and Idaho beat Northern Illinois 84-47 on Friday night. Idaho posted its first-ever win against the Huskies in the four-game series. Its 49-second-half points marked a season-high in 20-minutes of play this season. Michael Hanshaw's layup gave Idaho a 17-16 lead with 6:35 before halftime and the basket kickstarted a 20-8 run for Idaho (3-5) to close the half up 35-24. Northern Illinois' (3-6) Keshawn Williams scored 10 points. ------
